FOUR! Warner is off the mark in style! This is a gift for him first up! Shorter and outside off, this is cut through point for a boundary.

A little too short yet again and on middle, this is pulled but to square leg.

FOUR! Pulled away! Warner picks the length early, this is fractionally short, he gets into position quickly and then pulls it through square leg for a boundary. South Africa have been quite short so far in this game. They need to go fuller.
Another harmless delivery, this is well outside off. Not played at.
Back of a length and on off, Warner looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. A lot better line and length on this delivery by Rabada.
Goes a lot fuller this time but no swing available. This is pushed wide of mid off for one.
Good length and on off, Khawaja pushes it to covers.
Another one outside off to end, not played at.
Decent delivery! Length and just outside off, angling across, left alone.
Yet another one just outside off and slanting away. Not played at.
Yet another delivery which lands on a length but the line is outside off, David Warner shoulders arms to this one.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! That is a sharp, sharp catch from Marco Jansen! That went to him so quickly. Anrich Nortje gets the early breakthrough and it is of the dangerous David Warner! He continues bowling the line outside off but this time the length is fractionally short. Warner looks for the cut but the line and length was not the right one to play that shot. It flies off the outside edge to first slip where it is taken nicely. David Warner began really well and will be disappointed to have gotten out in that way. He could have left that delivery like he has been doing so far.
Howout: c Marco Jansen b Anrich Nortje

Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Anrich Nortje
